  "title": "Maintenance Technician / Electrical Technician",
  "description": "<ul><li><strong>Well Established Company</strong></li><li><strong>Basic $2500 - $3500 + Variable Bonus</strong></li><li><strong>Excellent Welfare and Benefits + Career progression</strong></li><li><strong>Working location: Tuas (Company Transport Provided)</strong></li><li><strong>Working Days: Monday to Friday</strong></li><li><strong>Working Hours: 8.30am to 5.30pm</strong></li></ul><p><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Perform preventive and corrective maintenance on electrical, hydraulic, and mechanical systems. </strong></li><li><strong>Troubleshoot and repair electrical panels, motors, sensors, and control systems. </strong></li><li><strong>Diagnose and maintain hydraulic and pneumatic systems including pumps, valves, actuators, and cylinders</strong>. </li><li>Support basic PLC fault diagnosis and coordinate with vendors or engineers where required. </li><li><strong>Carry out mechanical repairs such as replacement of bearings, belts, chains, and other components. </strong></li><li>Conduct routine inspections and preventive maintenance according to maintenance schedules. </li><li>Record maintenance activities, breakdown reports, and follow-up actions. </li><li>Comply with Workplace Safety and Health (WSH) regulations and company safety procedures. </li><li>Respond to machine breakdowns and support production operations when required.</li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Possess minimum Diploma in Engineering (Electrical, Mechanical, Mechatronics, Industrial Maintenance, or related field). </li><li><strong>Minimum 2 years of relevant maintenance experience in a manufacturing or industrial environment. </strong></li><li><strong>Candidates with strong electrical and hydraulic expertise will be preferred</strong>.</li></ul><p>Candidates are encouraged to apply this position via <strong>Apply Now </strong>button with the following information in the resume</p><ul><li>Work experiences and job responsibilities</li><li>Current and Expected salary</li><li>Reason for leaving</li><li>Date of availability</li><li>Education background</li></ul><p>We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.</p><p>LIONG ZHAO GUAN (R22107632)<br />EA Recruitment Pte Ltd<br />EA License No: 21C0492</p>",
